        <abstract> 
<p>Comments on SB’s book [<hi rend="italic">The fair haven</hi> (1873)]. CD is struck by SB’s dramatic power – thinks he could write "a really good novel". Surprised at strength of case SB makes that Jesus did not die on the cross. SB’s identity will soon be universally known: Leslie Stephen knows he is the author.</p> 
        </abstract>
